.TH "scsi_host_lookup" 9 "scsi_host_lookup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_host_lookup \- get a reference to a Scsi_Host by host no
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct Scsi_Host *" scsi_host_lookup
.BI "(unsigned short hostnum "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hostnum" 12
host number to locate
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return value:
A pointer to located Scsi_Host or NULL.

The caller must do a \fBscsi_host_put\fP to drop the reference
that \fBscsi_host_get\fP took. The \fBput_device\fP below dropped
the reference from \fBclass_find_device\fP.
